      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To: All Staff\n\nAs we prepare for our upcoming GDPR compliance audit, we want to ensure that our internal policies and procedures align with the regulatory requirements. In light of this, we are implementing a comprehensive review of our data protection practices. \n\nOur data protection framework is built on the following core principles: \n\n- Data minimization: We only collect and process the minimum amount of personal data necessary to achieve our objectives.\n- Consent: We obtain explicit consent from individuals before processing their personal data.\n- Lawful basis: We only process personal data on lawful grounds, such as for legitimate interests or with the individual's consent.\n- Accountability principle: We are fully accountable for our data protection practices and take responsibility for any data breaches.\n- Privacy by design: We design our systems and processes to protect personal data from the outset.\n- Transparency: We provide clear and transparent information to individuals about how we process their personal data.\n- Data protection officer: We have appointed a dedicated data protection officer to oversee our data protection practices.\n\nWe will be conducting a thorough review of our policies and procedures to ensure that they meet the requirements of the GDPR. This review will be conducted in accordance with the principles outlined above and will inform our future data protection practices.\n\nPlease direct",
